description:
**Problem**
8 parser functions are scattered in src/cli/mod.rs (lines 1598-1770), mixed with unrelated code:

- `parse_bead_type()` (line 1637)
- `parse_priority()` (line 1649)
- `parse_status()` (line 1668)
- `parse_dep_kind()` (line 1679)
- `parse_sort()` (line 1683)
- `parse_time_ms_opt()` (line 1708)
- `parse_time_ms()` (line 1723)
- `parse_dep_edge()` (line 1750)

These are all clap value_parser functions that convert strings to domain types. Having them in mod.rs hurts discoverability and bloats the file.

**Design**
1. Create `src/cli/parsers.rs`
2. Move all 8 parser functions there
3. Make them `pub(crate)` 
4. Update imports in mod.rs and any command handlers that use them directly

```rust
// src/cli/parsers.rs
use crate::core::{BeadType, Priority, WorkflowStatus};
use crate::daemon::query::{DepKind, SortField};

pub(crate) fn parse_bead_type(s: &str) -> Result<BeadType, String> { ... }
pub(crate) fn parse_priority(s: &str) -> Result<Priority, String> { ... }
pub(crate) fn parse_status(s: &str) -> Result<WorkflowStatus, String> { ... }
pub(crate) fn parse_dep_kind(s: &str) -> Result<DepKind, String> { ... }
pub(crate) fn parse_sort(s: &str) -> Result<SortField, String> { ... }
pub(crate) fn parse_time_ms_opt(s: &str) -> Result<Option<u64>, String> { ... }
pub(crate) fn parse_time_ms(s: &str) -> Result<u64, String> { ... }
pub(crate) fn parse_dep_edge(s: &str) -> Result<(String, String), String> { ... }
```

```rust
// src/cli/mod.rs
mod parsers;
use parsers::*; // or explicit imports
```

**Acceptance**
- [ ] src/cli/parsers.rs created with all 8 parser functions
- [ ] src/cli/mod.rs imports from parsers module
- [ ] No parser functions remain in mod.rs
- [ ] All #[arg(value_parser = ...)] references still work
- [ ] cargo clippy passes
- [ ] cargo test passes

**Files:** src/cli/mod.rs, src/cli/parsers.rs (new)
